                <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#003300;">
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="T_Menu">MD-Solids menu &gt; Auto-Layer</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Text"><text style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">OR</text></para>
                <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="T_Menu" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#003300;">
                  <li styleclass="T_Menu">Solids toolbar &gt; Auto-Layer</li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Auto-Layer</text> uses the <text styleclass="Parameter">Extrusion-Offset</text> and <text styleclass="Parameter">Part-Offset</text> parameters in <text styleclass="Interface">Application-Settings &gt; Auto-Profile dialog </text>to calculate the offset of each <text styleclass="Element">Extrusion</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
